author: Scary Pockets
description:
Enjoy this live version of Emily from Ryan's new record "Self Defense". 

Listen to the album: https://open.spotify.com/album/3nOzS0itdydKWDI1CJjf6G?si=_OEgv6yHR3ek0Q8STBd3Nw

"Emily"
(by Ryan Lerman & Jake Sherman)

Came back late last night
Everyone was so stressed out
Clothes on, passed out on the couch
Didn't want to wake you

Then this morning you seemed off
I tried to ask about your week
No luck, you looked away
And I knew that there was something wrong

Is it true? Emily
How could you think that you could decieve me
Oooo, Emily
How could you be so cruel?

I can take it, beat me up
I promise that I won't fight back
Tell me what just wasnt enough
That you'd leave me for another man

Emily, I thought that we had something
Guess that it was nothing after all
Emily, could you tell me

MUSICIAN CREDITS
Lead vocal, guitar, composer: Ryan Lerman
Drums: Tamir Barzilay
Bass: Jesse Singer
Keys: Philip Kronengold
Composer: Jake Sherman

AUDIO CREDITS
Recording Engineer: Nathan Alef
Mixing/
title: RYAN LERMAN // Emily (Live)
